ISLAMABAD, Feb 1 (APP): The Election Commission of Pakistan (ECP) has announced February 8th (Thursday) as a public holiday, aiming to provide voters the opportunity to cast their votes conveniently.
The ECP spokesperson said in a statement that the declared holiday, referencing sections (4) and 8 Â© of the Election Act 2017, is granted to empower voters in exercising their right to franchise freely and conveniently.
